did.unittitle: Commonwealth Fund records, Communications, SG 3, Series 8

physdesc.extent: 49 letter-size document boxes, 1 standard record storage box.

processinfo.head: Processing Information
processinfo.p: Minimal processing. Some records remain in original file folders.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: Open for research. Brittle or damaged items are available at the discretion of RAC.

userestrict.head: Conditions Governing Use
userestrict.p: RAC has legal title, copyright and literary property rights to this collection in so far as it holds them.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Information regarding the Rockefeller Archive Center's preferred elements and forms of citation can be found at http://www.rockarch.org/research/citations.php

acqinfo.head: Immediate Source of Acquisition
acqinfo.p: The Commonwealth Fund records were donated to RAC in 1985. The initial transfer of archival records to RAC began in 1986, and transfers continue on a regular basis. This series was donated to RAC in multiple accessions from 2002 through 2009.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Material in this Communications series includes: Press Clippings 2000-2002, Commonwealth Fund Publications 2001-2008, and a variety of historical files documenting the history of the Fund, its programs, and it's headquarters - the Harkness House. This series also contains a print archive of the Commonwealth Fund website 2003-2009, including monthly snapshots of the website. Available records also document the Fund's 75th Anniversary celebration and related publications.
